1) Blade layouts â€” deep dive (hands-on)
Goal: make a single reusable layout (header, footer, nav) and apply it to studentRecords.blade.php so pages share the same look and maintenance is easy.

Concept (short):

@extends('layouts.app') â€” page uses a layout file.
@yield('content') â€” placeholder inside layout where page content shows.
@section('content') ... @endsection â€” page fills the placeholder.
@include('partials.xyz') â€” include small reusable partials (e.g., messages).
Use layout for CSS/JS links, nav, footer, and common scripts.
@stack('scripts') & @push('scripts') Used to add page-specific JS scripts dynamically
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Steps
ğŸªœ 1. Create the Layout File

ğŸ“ Location:
resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php

ğŸ“„ Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>@yield('title', 'My Laravel App')</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <a class="navbar-brand" href="{{ url('/') }}">My Laravel App</a>
        <div class="collapse navbar-collapse">
          <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
            <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="{{ url('/student-records') }}">Student Records</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Page Content -->
    <div class="container mt-4">
        @yield('content')
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="text-center mt-5 py-3 bg-light border-top">
        <small>&copy; 2025 My Laravel App. All rights reserved.</small>
    </footer>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    
    @stack('scripts')
</body>
</html>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Use Layout in Your Page
Example:
resources/views/studentRecords.blade.php

@extends('layouts.app')

@section('title', 'Student Records')

@section('content')
<div class="card shadow">
    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
        <h4>Student Records</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>Welcome to the Student Records page!</p>
        <!-- Add your CRUD form and table here -->
    </div>
</div>
@endsection


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. (Optional) Create Reusable Components

If you want to separate sections like navbar or footer:

resources/views/partials/navbar.blade.php
resources/views/partials/footer.blade.php


Then include them inside your layout:

@include('partials.navbar')
@include('partials.footer')

âœ… BENEFITS:

Cleaner code

Reusable design

Easy to maintain and update

Professional project structure